1 AN ACT relating to sanctioning bodies for boxing and wrestling exhibitions.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 229.011 is amended to read as follows:
4 As used in this chapter unless the context clearly indicates otherwise the following
5 definitions shall apply:
6 (1) "Advertise" means the use of handbills, placards, posters, billboards, pictures,
7 printed or written material or newspapers or other publications, or radio, television,
8 Internet, and other communication media;
9 (2) "Boxing" means a contest or exhibition in which a person delivers blows with the
10 fist that may be reasonably expected to disable or inflict injury and in which boxers
11 compete for money, a prize, or other pecuniary gain, or for which admission is
12 charged to spectators;
13 (3) "Commission" means the Kentucky Boxing and Wrestling Commission;
14 (4) "Exhibition" means an event or engagement:
15 (a) In which the participants show or display their skills without necessarily
16 striving to win;[ or]
17 (b) That involves amateurs not under the jurisdiction of the Kentucky High
18 School Athletic Association, the National Collegiate Athletic Association, the
19 National Association of Intercollegiate Athletics, the Amateur Athletic Union,
20 Golden Gloves, USA Boxing, or USA Wrestling[, or a public show to which
21 an admission ticket is required, or other charge is made, or invitation]; or
22 (c) That involves a public show in which an admission ticket is required, or
23 other charge is made, that is not sanctioned by one (1) of the sanctioning
24 bodies listed in paragraph (b) of this subsection;
25 (5) "Kickboxing" means a boxing contest or exhibition where the participants are
26 allowed to throw kicks or foot blows at the opponent in addition to punching with
27 the hands and in which kickboxers compete for money, a prize, or other pecuniary
