1 gain, or for which admission is charged to spectators;
2 (6) "Mixed martial arts" means any form of unarmed contest or exhibition in which
3 participants compete for money, a prize, or other pecuniary gain, or for which
4 admission is charged to spectators. Mixed martial arts may include any element or
5 combination of elements of boxing, kickboxing, wrestling, or other martial arts.
6 Exhibitions where participants are judged on form and style and where punches and
7 kicks are pulled shall not be included in this definition;
8 (7) "Muay thai" means a boxing contest or exhibition where the participants are
9 allowed combined use of clinches, elbows, knees, and shins in addition to punching
10 with the hands and in which participants compete for money, a prize, or other
11 pecuniary gain, or for which admission is charged to spectators;
12 (8) "Person" means an individual, partnership, corporation, association, or club;
13 (9) "Show" means any boxing, kickboxing, mixed martial arts, muay thai, or wrestling
14 match, contest, or exhibition coming under the jurisdiction of the Kentucky Boxing
15 and Wrestling Commission;
16 (10) "Unarmed combat" means boxing, kickboxing, sparring, wrestling, mixed martial
17 arts, or muay thai under the jurisdiction of the commission; and
18 (11) "Wrestling" means an activity or performance of athletic and wrestling skill
19 between individuals who are not under the jurisdiction of the Kentucky High
20 School Athletic Association, the National Collegiate Athletic Association, the
21 National Association of Intercollegiate Athletics, or USA Wrestling in which the
22 participants struggle hand-to-hand primarily for the purpose of providing
23 entertainment to spectators rather than conducting a bona fide athletic contest. The
24 outcome of these matches may be predetermined. Participating wrestlers may not be
25 required to use their best efforts in order to win.
26 Section 2. KRS 229.045 is amended to read as follows:
